title.narrative: COMMUNICATION FOR DEVELOPMENT

description.narrative: Sierra Leone Communication for Development will provide high quality social and behavioural expertise for effective communication on child rights, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The Sierra Leone Country Programme is efficiently designed, coordinated, managed and supported to meet quality results based management standards to achieve results for children

title.narrative: Sierra Leone Communication for Development will provide high quality social and behavioural expertise for effectivecommunication on child rights

description.narrative: In 2021, 11,688 community mobilizers/volunteers were trained and mobilized to disseminate life-saving information and to engage communities compared to 9,046 in 2020, with a total of 1,115,000 (versus 847,935 in 2020) women, men and youth engaged in dialogue on priority health behaviors. Furthermore, 3.7 million people were reached through a network of 59 district/community radio stations. UNICEF provided support to the government to strengthen its Social Behavior Change response and leverage partnerships for demand/uptake of essential health and social services. Efforts were made for evidence-informed response, by using assessments, surveys and piloting a real-time system for managing rumours and misinformation. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2022
